The article highlights the importance of remembering and mourning the 700,000 American lives lost to COVID-19. It emphasizes the need to not become desensitized to the sorrow and encourages getting vaccinated. The vaccines are described as safe, free, and easy to obtain, with significant progress made in the fight against COVID-19 due to vaccination efforts. Over three-quarters of Americans aged 12 and above have received at least one vaccine dose, including nearly 94 percent of seniors. The article urges readers to get vaccinated to save lives, beat COVID-19, and move forward as a united nation.